==Trivia==
*In the comics, '''Francis Castiglione''' is a veteran of the {{WPS|Vietnam War}}, who returned home only to watch his family die for witnessing a mob execution lead by the Costa family, a crime family in the [[Maggia]]. He vowed to kill criminals, disregarding his identity as Castle and calling himself only the Punisher. Castle appears as an adversary of [[Spider-Man]], when he targets the hero for inadvertently causing [[Gwen Stacy]]'s death, they later become situational allies after a misunderstanding.
*Punisher was originally set to be introduced in a post-credits scene at the end of [[Daredevil (TV series)/Season One|first season]] [[Daredevil (episode)|finale]] of ''[[Daredevil (TV series)|Daredevil]]'', where he kills [[Leland Owlsley]], with the character's face unseen but his skull insignia appearing. However, the idea was forced to be dropped as [[Netflix]] at the time was not designed to accommodate post-credits scenes, since the timer to begin the next episode would start as soon as the credits began to play.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20240529091607/https://www.hypable.com/punisher-daredevil-season-one/ Exclusive: ‘Daredevil’ season 1 coda almost introduced Punisher, says showrunner]</ref>
*Castle's fake name "Pete Castiglione" is a reference to the comics, in which Castle's real name was Francis Castiglione and he and his family were Italian immigrants from [[Sicily]]. It was also referenced in ''[[The Judas Goat]]'', where Castle mentioned that [[Maria Castle]]'s grandmother was Sicilian.
*Castle is a fan of [[Earth, Wind & Fire]], [[Bruce Springsteen]], [[Wu-Tang Clan]], and [[Shooter Jennings]].
*Castle was raised Catholic, but lost his faith after the death of his family.
*Castle is a fan of the {{WPS|New York Rangers}}.
*Castle likes pancakes, Lombardi's sausage, and mushroom pizza.
*Castle is ambidextrous.
*Castle weighs 225 lbs and stands at 6'3" with an athletic build.<ref name=TPS1P/> In real life, [[Jon Bernthal]] is 5'11".

==Behind the Scenes==
*Punisher in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] is the fourth live-action incarnation of the character, following incarnations portrayed by {{WPS|Dolph Lundgren}}, {{WPS|Thomas Jane}} and [[Ray Stevenson]].
*Punisher will be the fourth pre-Disney+ [[Marvel Television]] character to make an appearance in the films.
*[[Jon Bernthal]] made audition tapes together with [[Tom Holland]] while filming ''{{WPS|Pilgrimage (2017 film)|Pilgrimage}}'', both landing their roles of Frank Castle and [[Peter Parker]], respectively. In the comics, Punisher first appeared as an adversary of Spider-Man.<ref>[http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/exclusive-bernthal-holland-teamed-marvel-auditions-article-1.2560381 EXCLUSIVE: Jon Bernthal and Tom Holland made audition tapes together to land The Punisher and Spider-Man roles]</ref>
*Bernthal was brought back for the original production of ''[[Daredevil: Born Again]]'' and shot some scenes during the show's original 2023 filming. However, he became displeased with how Frank Castle was written and portrayed, and therefore quit the show. When the series underwent creative overhaul, the hiring of [[Dario Scardapane]] in addition to Bernthal having creative input on the character's future resulted in Bernthal returning to the show and filming scenes for the post-overhaul episodes in 2024.<ref>[https://ew.com/jon-bernthal-daredevil-return-no-holds-barred-punisher-tv-special-exclusive-11698647 Jon Bernthal on his 'toe dip' Daredevil return and 'no-holds-barred' Punisher in TV special (exclusive)]</ref> Despite this, a scene Bernthal shot in 2023 for the original version was used in his ''Born Again'' debut episode ''[[Sic Semper Systema]]''.<ref name="Nachmanoff Phase Hero">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uy2hL5BRt5w Daredevil Director Reveals Punisher, Kingpin Insights (Jeffrey Nachmanoff Episode 4 Interview)]</ref><ref name="BernthalBoyd">[[:File:Jon Bernthal and David Boyd (BTS).jpg|Jon Bernthal directed by David Boyd on May 25, 2023]]</ref><ref name="BernthalCox2023">[[:File:Castle and Murdock.jpg|Bernthal and Cox Scene - Filmed May 25, 2023]]</ref><ref name="Bernthal2023">[[:File:Frank Castle (DDBA).jpg|Jon Bernthal on the original ''Born Again'' {{!}} May 25, 2023]]</ref> At one point, there were plans to include a bottle episode that focused on Frank and [[Echo]] spending an unusual and dramatic night together, but not in a romantic way, before the idea was scrapped because of the overhaul.<ref>[https://bleedingcool.com/tv/daredevil-born-again-originally-had-echo-punisher-focused-episode/ Daredevil: Born Again Originally Had Echo/Punisher-Focused Episode]</ref>
*[[Steven S. DeKnight]] said this version of Punisher would be "completely the Marvel version," as previous portrayals did not appear under the [[Marvel Studios]] / [[Marvel Television]] banner. He also felt Bernthal's Punisher would not be as "graphically violent" as in ''{{WPS|Punisher: War Zone}}''.<ref>[http://www.slashfilm.com/daredevil-season-2-punisher/ Steven DeKnight Says ‘Daredevil’ Finally Features “The Marvel Version” of the Punisher]</ref>
*[[Douglas Petrie]] stated that {{WPS|Travis Bickle}} from ''{{WPS|Taxi Driver}}'' was an influence on the character, as well as current events, saying, ''"Taking lethal justice into your own hands in America in 2015 is tricky shit. We have not shied away from the rich complicated reality of Now. If you've got a gun and you're not the police you're going to incite strong feelings."''
*Petrie and [[Marco Ramirez]] talked about creating their version of the character following the film versions, with Ramirez saying, ''"even if you know the character, you’ve never seen him like this. That was the big thing we wanted. There are four movies, eight hours and four actors. We’ve seen this guy. We think we know who he is, but even we learned that he’s so much more."'' Petrie said, ''"We hope to make people forget what they’ve seen before, whether they’ve loved it or not."''<ref>[http://collider.com/daredevil-season-2-punisher-elektra-story/ ‘Daredevil’ Showrunners on How Punisher and Elektra Shake Up Season 2]</ref>
*In order to get in the correct mindset to portray Castle, Bernthal trained with military members, along with receiving weapon training. Bernthal also ''"had to put myself in as dark of place as possible"'' to connect with ''"the emptiness inside"'' Castle, and isolate himself, including walking across the Brooklyn Bridge to get to set ''"to shed any outside influence of joy."''<ref>[http://www.ew.com/article/2016/01/16/daredevil-jon-bernthal-punisher Daredevil Jon Bernthal interview: Went to a dark place for Punisher]</ref>
*Describing the character, Bernthal said, ''"As a man who put his [life] on the line and really went through the ultimate sacrifice for this country in his involvement in the military. He’s a guy who brought the war home with him [in] the worst possible way. There are a lot of iterations of this character and in all of them it’s a man who’s gone through this unbelievable trauma and what’s interesting about our take on him is how this trauma reshapes his own philosophy."''
*Bernthal also talked about the character's 'superpowers,' saying, ''"If I got one thing from the comics, I think, as far as superpowers... his superpower is his rage. His superpower is that he is not going to quit, and he is going to go forward no matter what. And that's as human and grounded a quality as I think as this sort of genre could have."''<ref>[http://ca.ign.com/articles/2016/01/18/daredevil-the-punisher-and-elektra-will-make-matt-murdock-question-his-role DAREDEVIL: THE PUNISHER AND ELEKTRA WILL MAKE MATT MURDOCK QUESTION HIS ROLE AS A HERO]</ref>
*[[Eric Linden]], [[Spencer Mulligan]], [[Justin Eaton]], and [[Can Aydin]] were stunt doubles for [[Jon Bernthal]] in the role of the Punisher.
*[[Rocky Kellon Smith]] was a stand-in for [[Jon Bernthal]] in the role of the Punisher.

